comments: Eubanks (POR) maintains a rested hand on Maledon's (OKC) side after the gather and jumps alongside Maledon's path during the driving shot attempt as marginal contact occurs. McLemore (POR) then cleanly blocks the driving shot attempt.
McLemore (POR) brings his hand toward Wiggins' (OKC) back and marginal contact occurs as McLemore changes direction as they approach the screen.
Elleby (POR) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Pokusevski (OKC) prior to any incidental contact occurring.
Sarr (OKC) extends his hands forward in pursuit of the rebound and incidental contact occurs with Elleby's (POR) arm.
Williams (POR) brings his off-arm toward Wiggins' (OKC) right arm/front and marginal contact occurs as Williams slows his momentum.
Elleby (POR) establishes himself in a screening position in Wiggins' (OKC) path and slips the marginal contact that occurs along the perimeter.
Wiggins (OKC) is moving alongside Williams' (POR) path and marginal contact occurs with Williams' side during his driving shot attempt.
Sarr (OKC) and Eubanks (POR) come together at the same spot and incidental contact occurs along the perimeter, which they each absorb.

Johnson (POR) turns alongside Wiggins' (OKC) path and marginal body contact occurs at the end of Wiggins' drive. Simultaneously, Williams (POR) brushes Wiggins' arm and marginal contact occurs prior to Wiggins' pass.
Williams (POR) and Roby (OKC) each make clean contact with the ball and dislodge it away prior to any incidental arm contact occurring.

Roby (OKC) is already losing control of the ball prior to incidental arm contact being made by Elleby (POR). Roby and Elleby then come together at the same spot to pursue the loose ball and marginal side-to-side contact occurs.
Sarr (OKC) jumps vertically and maintains a legal vertical position as he absorbs the body contact from Williams (POR) on the driving shot attempt.
Pokusevski (OKC) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
McLemore (POR) establishes himself in a screening position in Pokusevski's (OKC) path and absorbs the contact.
Wiggins (OKC) is retreating his arm toward a vertical position and absorbs the marginal contact that occurs as McLemore (POR) rips through.
Eubanks (POR) establishes himself in a screening position in Wiggins' (OKC) path and absorbs the contact.
Wiggins (OKC) legally contests McLemore's (POR) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Johnson (POR) extends his forearm into Roby's (OKC) back and delivers contact as Roby elevates for the rebound.
Wiggins (OKC) commits a take foul on Williams (POR).
Roby (OKC) establishes himself in a screening position in Dunn's (POR) path and absorbs the contact as the defensive switch occurs.
Dunn (POR) makes clean contact with the ball as Roby (OKC) receives the pass.

McLemore (POR) continues to re-establish as he turns and he delivers contact to Sarr (OKC), causing Sarr to lose his balance. This contact precedes and subsequently causes the ensuing leg-to-leg contact that occurs with Eubanks (POR).
Roby (OKC) grasps and then quickly releases Eubanks' (POR) arm as he moves to contest the shot.
Pokusevski (OKC) legally contests Johnson's (POR) jump shot attempt.

Sarr (OKC) cleanly blocks Elleby's (POR) put-back attempt and dislodges the ball away. Sarr follows-through on his shot contest and marginal contact occurs with Elleby's head. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Johnson (POR) moves alongside Wiggins' (OKC) path and absorbs the contact as Wiggins cuts back toward him at the end of the drive.
Williams (POR) brings his left arm toward Maledon's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs with Maledon's front as he starts his drive.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Williams (POR) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Johnson (POR) saves the ball back into play prior to his foot landing out of bounds.
Wiggins (OKC) brings his arm toward McLemore's (POR) path and marginal contact occurs with McLemore's front as he goes over the pick.
Eubanks (POR) establishes himself in a screening position in Wiggins' (OKC) path and absorbs the contact.
Krejci (OKC) brushes Williams' (POR) right leg and marginal contact occurs after Williams' gather.
Elleby (POR) brings his hand toward Roby's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs with Roby's arm/front after his gather.
Eubanks (POR) firms up in his screening position in Krejci's (OKC) path and absorbs the contact, some of which occurs to Krejci's leg.
Johnson (POR) attempts to gather and is already losing control of the ball prior to incidental arm contact being made by Roby (OKC).
Maledon (OKC) extends and delivers body contact to Williams' (POR) side after his gather, affecting the driving shot attempt.
Eubanks (POR) legally contests Maledon's (OKC) driving shot attempt.
Williams (POR) commits a take foul on Maledon (OKC).
A delay of game warning is assessed to both OKC and POR.

Johnson (POR) contests the dunk attempt and marginal contact occurs with Wiggins' (OKC) head and back as he finishes at the rim. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Roby (OKC) jumps vertically and absorbs the marginal body contact made with Williams (POR) before cleanly blocking his layup attempt.
Roby (OKC) is retreating away from Eubanks (POR) and absorbs the marginal body contact that occurs during Eubanks' put-back attempt.
Eubanks (POR) commits a take foul on Wiggins (OKC).
Pokusevski (OKC) maintains a legal guarding position as Williams (POR) starts his upward shooting motion.
